stopher. But it really means ' servant of Christ.'"],"variants":[]},{"name":"Gilicrist","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Scottish Gaelic:  see  Gilchrist  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gilchrist","meanings":["Scottish (western) and Irish (Down): from Gaelic <i>Mac Giolla Chríosd</i>, <i>Mac Gille Chríosd</i> ‘son of the servant of Christ’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Gillechriosd Gilicrist MacLachlan 1st. Chief of Clan MacLachlan was born in 1156, in Argyll, Scotland as the son of Dunsleve. He married Unknown MacLachlan about 1176, in Stralachlan, Argyll, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died after 1186, in his hometown, and was buried in Argyll, Scotland."},"et":{"1156–after 1186":"1156–pärast 1186","1156–1186":"1156–1186","1156–Female":"1156–Surnud","1177–1248":"1177–1248","1186–1249":"1186–1249","–Male":"Surnud","1249":"1249","1248":"1248","1156":"1156","1177":"1177","1186":"1186","1241":"1241","after 1186":"pärast 1186","about 1176":"umbes 1176","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Stralachlan, Argyll, Scotland":"Stralachlan, Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"1156–after 1186":"1156–1186 jälkeen","1156–1186":"1156–1186","1156–Female":"1156–Kuollut","1177–1248":"1177–1248","1186–1249":"1186–1249","–Male":"Kuollut","1249":"1249","1248":"1248","1156":"1156","1177":"1177","1186":"1186","1241":"1241","after 1186":"1186 jälkeen","about 1176":"noin 1176","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Stralachlan, Argyll, Scotland":"Stralachlan, Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"1156–after 1186":"1156–après 1186","1156–1186":"1156–1186","1156–Female":"1156–Décédée","1177–1248":"1177–1248","1186–1249":"1186–1249","–Male":"Décédé","1249":"1249","1248":"1248","1156":"1156","1177":"1177","1186":"1186","1241":"1241","after 1186":"après 1186","about 1176":"environ 1176","Scotland":"Écosse, R